I'll create a web app.

Project name: TodoList

To get started, I'll create a new React Native project using the following command:

```bash
npx react-native init TodoList
```

This will create a new React Native project with a basic file structure and a `App.js` file.

Next, I'll create a new file called `constants.js` to store the app's configuration:

```javascript
// constants.js
const API_URL = 'https://api.example.com';
```

I'll then create a new file called `store.js` to manage the app's state:

```javascript
// store.js
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import axios from 'axios';

const store = (apiUrl) => {
  const [data, setData] = useState([]);
  const [error, setError] = useState(null);

  const fetchData = async () => {
    try {
      const response = await axios.get(apiUrl);
      setData(response.data);
    } catch (error) {
      setError(error.message);
    }
  };

  const fetchDataError = async () => {
    try {
      const response = await axios.get(apiUrl);
      setError(response.message);
    } catch (error) {
      setError(error.message);
    }
  };

  return { data, error, fetchData, fetchDataError };
};

export default store;
```

I'll then create a new file called `pages/Main.js` to display the app's main content:

```javascript
// pages/Main.js
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text } from 'react-native';

const Main = () => {
  return (
    <View>
      <Text>Main Screen</Text>
    </View>
  );
};

export default Main;
```

I'll create a new file called `pages/Settings.js` to display the app's settings:

```javascript
// pages/Settings.js
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text } from 'react-native';

const Settings = () => {
  return (
    <View>
      <Text>Settings Screen</Text>
    </View>
  );
};

export default Settings;
```

I'll create a new file called `screens/Main.js` to render the app's main content:

```javascript
// screens/Main.js
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text } from 'react-native';
import { store } from './store';

const MainScreen = () => {
  const { data, error, fetchData, fetchDataError } = store();

  if (error) {
    return <Text>Error: {error}</Text>;
  }

  if (!data) {
    return <Text>Loading...</Text>;
  }

  return (
    <View>
      <Text>Todo List</Text>
      <View>
        <Text>Task 1</Text>
        <Text>Task 2</Text>
        <Text>Task 3</Text>
      </View>
    </View>
  );
};

export default MainScreen;
```

I'll create a new file called `screens/Settings.js` to render the app's settings:

```javascript
// screens/Settings.js
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text } from 'react-native';

const SettingsScreen = () => {
  return (
    <View>
      <Text>Settings Screen</Text>
    </View>
  );
};

export default SettingsScreen;
```

Finally, I'll create a new file called `App.js` to render the app's main screen:

```javascript
// App.js
import React from 'react';
import { View } from 'react-native';
import MainScreen from './screens/Main';
import SettingsScreen from './screens/Settings';

const App = () => {
  return (
    <View>
      <MainScreen />
      <SettingsScreen />
    </View>
  );
};

export default App;
```

That's it! I've created a basic Todo List app with a main screen and a settings screen.

